10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. AIVA is best suited for film and game composers, orchestral and classical music, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Udio, meanwhile, shines for musicians exploring AI composition, high quality AI music, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2016, AIVA describes itself as \"AI composer for emotional soundtracks and music.\" Udio, established in 2023, positions itself as \"AI music creation with studio-quality output.\" With 7 years between them, AIVA brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Udio offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Udio** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (2 vs 1), more competitive pricing, availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean AIVA is a poor choice — far from it. AIVA excels in its own right, particularly for film and game composers and orchestral and classical music.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent audio quality, go with Udio. If excellent orchestral compositions matters more to you, AIVA is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
